#: ../../../command/math.rst:2
msgid "math"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:4
msgid "Perform mathematical operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:7
msgid "Expression Evaluation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:9
msgid "math(EXPR <variable> \"<expression>\" [OUTPUT_FORMAT <format>])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:13
msgid ""
"Evaluates a mathematical ``<expression>`` and sets ``<variable>`` to the "
"resulting value.  The result of the expression must be representable as a 64-"
"bit signed integer. Floating point inputs are invalid e.g. ``1.1 * 10``. Non-"
"integer results e.g. ``3 / 2`` are truncated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:18
msgid ""
"The mathematical expression must be given as a string (i.e. enclosed in "
"double quotation marks). An example is ``\"5 * (10 + 13)\"``. Supported "
"operators are ``+``, ``-``, ``*``, ``/``, ``%``, ``|``, ``&``, ``^``, ``~``, "
"``<<``, ``>>``, and ``(...)``; they have the same meaning as in C code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:24
msgid ""
"Hexadecimal numbers are recognized when prefixed with ``0x``, as in C code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:27
msgid ""
"The result is formatted according to the option ``OUTPUT_FORMAT``, where "
"``<format>`` is one of"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:31
msgid "``HEXADECIMAL``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:32
msgid "Hexadecimal notation as in C code, i. e. starting with \"0x\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:33
msgid "``DECIMAL``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:34
msgid ""
"Decimal notation. Which is also used if no ``OUTPUT_FORMAT`` option is "
"specified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:37
msgid "For example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:39
msgid ""
"math(EXPR value \"100 * 0xA\" OUTPUT_FORMAT DECIMAL)      # value is set to "
"\"1000\"\n"
"math(EXPR value \"100 * 0xA\" OUTPUT_FORMAT HEXADECIMAL)  # value is set to "
"\"0x3e8\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:45
msgid "Increment/Decrement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:47
msgid ""
"math(INCREMENT <variable>)\n"
"math(DECREMENT <variable>)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/math.rst:54
msgid ""
"Take the value of ``<variable>``, increment/decrement it, and store the "
"result back in ``<variable>``. The variable must be defined and be a valid "
"base-10 integer."
msgstr ""
